Ex-BBNaija housemate Ifu Ennada has slammed men who expect to be applauded for staying faithful to their partners. The movie star, in a recent social media post, also blasted men who adopt the fallacious notion that “men are polygamous in nature” to cheat as if it were their birthright. Ifu Ennada reminded such men that women actually possess the adequacy to “outcheat” them. But in so doing, those women will only be giving up their bodies for the highest form of disrespect.   Singer Faze loses mom one year after twin sister’s demise     Ex-BBNaija’s Nina blasts Nigerians in Diaspora…     Six celebrities who became parents by surrogacy   - Advertisement - The reality TV star wrote: “I hate it when a man thinks he should be applauded for staying faithful. “Yeah, you should applaud me for sticking with your ass when I can easily have 10 of you with just 1 phone call. “Some men speak of cheating as though it’s their birthright – “men are polygamous in nature”, but they forget woman have the capacity to “outcheat” them if they want. But we stay elevated regardless because, what’s the point in disrespecting one’s body?”